biblScope></bibl>). Не связаны ли эти слова с <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>qonaq</w> <gloss><q>дом</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/> <gloss><q>ночлег</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр.? Или с <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*kana-</w> <gloss><q>жилище</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/> <gloss><q>дом</q></gloss></mentioned>,  [<mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*kanak(k’n’k)</w></mentioned>]?</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Cf. in %bPersian-Kurdish%b dialects <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>kuane, kuonək</w> <gloss><q>hearth</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. II, стр. 392</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. II, p. 392</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Жуковский"/><biblScope>II 111</biblScope></bibl>). Are these words related to <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>qonaq</w> <gloss><q>house</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/> <gloss><q>lodging for the night</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc.? And are they related to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*kana-</w> <gloss><q>dwelling</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/> <gloss><q>house</q></gloss></mentioned>,  [<mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*kanak(k’n’k)</w></mentioned>]?</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>